ic differences, and women's emancipation. In doing so he sheds new light on the roles of Helen Creighton, the Maritime region's most famous folklorist, and Mary Black, an influential handicrafts revivalist, in creating this false identity.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Customs & Traditions.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978077357543140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780773575431423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780773575431/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles